          "notes": "Module excels in concept accuracy and technical depth, with strong real-world examples and up-to-date references (Google HDR+, Sony Eye AF, Night Sight). However, it critically fails in D5 (Applied Outcome): labs are generic AI chatbot interactions with no clear executability, quiz questions test recall rather than judgment, and learners gain no tangible new capability. Narrative framing exists but feels bolted onto educational content rather than driving discovery.",
          "topIssue": "Labs must be restructured from open-ended chatbot prompts to concrete, measurable tasks: e.g., 'Shoot a test scene with computational photography enabled, then with RAW to bypass it, compare artifacts, and document 3 specific differences you observe.' Current labs are unexecutable and untestable.",
